Roads of LoveI feel the threat of tears behind my eyes, The pressure on my chest, The needle probing my heart. She's prettier, She funnier What do I have that she doesn't? She has his attention, She has his time, She has his heart. And I'm left in the dust. Thrown aside, thrown away. And as he left He ripped my heart in two. Broken and tattered I lay by the road When you walked by You said I was prettiest You said I was funniest Your sewed me up. You dulled the needle Now a feather tickling my heart That pressure in my chest lifted Leaving me all bubbly And the threat of tears Spilled over in happiness. For I had your time I had your attention, I had your heart. And you had mine.Roads of Love4 years ago in Free Verse
